            "summary": "Major cryptocurrencies saw a sharp decline on Friday, with the total crypto market cap falling by 3.77% to $3.18 trillion. Bitcoin maintained a dominance of 63.7% while Ethereum held a market share of 9.2%. At 11 p.m. ET, the recorded prices showed Bitcoin down by 2.78% at $102,148, Ethereum down by 7.18% at $2,435, and Dogecoin down by 9.14% at $0.1726. The selloff was linked to an escalating public dispute between President Donald Trump and Tesla CEO Elon Musk. Tesla shares took a hit, dropping 14.3% as Trump threatened to cut government contracts for Musk's companies. The feud started when Musk criticized Trump's spending bill on social media, leading to Musk leaving his role as a senior adviser. The Solana-based OFFICIAL TRUMP memecoin also dropped by 9.75% to $9.82 amid the political tensions.",
