            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/news/retail-sales/25/06/45807103/dollar-stores-cash-in-as-shoppers-seek-bargains-at-dollar-general-dollar-tree-five-below",
            "summary": "Consumer behavior is shifting towards dollar stores like Dollar General Corp. (NYSE: DG), Dollar Tree, Inc. (NASDAQ: DLTR), and Five Below, Inc. (NASDAQ: FIVE) due to economic uncertainty and inflation. Even higher-income households are turning to these discount retailers to manage their budgets effectively. Recently, these stores have reported better-than-expected earnings and sales growth. In particular, DLTR saw a strong first quarter with same-store net sales increasing by 5.4%, driven by a 2.5% rise in traffic and a 2.8% increase in average ticket size. CEO Mike Creedon noted that Dollar Tree's affordable prices are appealing to customers across all income levels, including those earning over $100,000. This trend highlights a broader shift in consumer shopping habits towards seeking value during financially challenging times.",
